[4] Cholera - Tanzania (Mwanza Region)
Date: Tue 23 Feb 2016
Source: AllAfrica, The Citizen report [edited]
http://allafrica.com/stories/201602231441.html


According to the health department, 7 cases of cholera have been reported in Ilemela District. The acting Mwanza Regional Medical Officer, Onesmo Rwekendera told The Citizen that the patients have been admitted to Karume Health Centre. He said despite efforts to curb the disease, new cases of cholera are cropping up.

"We have involved all health departments in the region to find ways to curb this disease. We have deployed special task forces to create more public awareness on the importance of hygiene including drinking clean and safe water," he said. But the medical officer admits that this task has been difficult due to the high influx of visitors entering Mwanza City.

According to the city council's health officer Osward Mpelasoka a quarantine area for cholera patients has been set up in Igoma Ward on the outskirt of the city: "We are responding to people with diarrhea and dehydration as first steps of action in controlling further spreading." He added that the city council is monitoring and disinfecting areas that have had cases of cholera.

[Byline: Geofrey Kimani]

