[6] Diarrhea - Nepal
Date: Tue 16 Feb 2016
Source: The Kathmandu Post [edited]
http://kathmandupost.ekantipur.com/news/2016-02-16/diarrhoea-kills-2-kids-scores-ill.html


Diarrhea outbreak in 3 VDCs [Village Development Committees] of western Dailekh [district] has claimed lives of 2 children and downed many others in the last couple of days. Lakandra, Tolijaisi, and Bishala VDCs are grappling with the disease as health officials are scrambling to treat the patients, most of whom are children.

A 7-month-old and an 8-month-old from Tolijaisi VDC died on Saturday night [13 Feb 2016] at a local clinic, the District Public Health Office (DPHO) said. Besides diarrhea, some children are also suffering from pneumonia and fever.

Dr Kikash Sah, who works at a local health centre, said 12 children have been referred to Surkhet [district] for treatment while others are receiving treatment in local health facilities. "Most of the patients are [younger than] 2 years of age. It is still unclear what caused the outbreak," Dr Sah said.

DPHO [District Public Health Office] Chief Dr Nirmal Rasaili health workers are already working in the affected villages while another team from Surkhet Regional Health Director is expected to reach by [Tue 16 Feb 2016].

[Byline: Prakash Adhikari]

